commit.message:
quietly check for libfts.pc during configuration

Musl libc doesn't have own fts.h implementation, so libfts is used instead.

include sys/stat.h in cluster.hh to capture possible renames

Musl C library seems to rename stat64 to stat with preprocesor macros.
All places where struct stat64 is used must therefore include sys/stat.h.

reverse yoda conditions back to conventional order

Compliers warn about accidental assignments in conditions, so Yoda-style
conditions are not needed anymore.

hide safe struct fiemap out-of-bounds accesses from a compiler

Struct fiemap has a member fm_extents that is declared as a zero-length
array. It's safe to access this array given buffer size is large enough.
However GCC doesn't really know that. Instead it sees out-of-bounds
accesses.
bump required CMake version to make newer CMake happier

remove -Werror=implicit-function-declaration from flags

GCC says that it's not valid for C++.

commit.message:
mountpoint-select-dialog: don't show the last entry twice

Currently, the mountpoint selection dialog shows the last entry in the list twice.

This is caused by incorrect EOF handling:
EOF is hit while trying to do formatted input after the last complete line is read.
Formatted input doesn't get anything from the stream,
but there are no checks for that,
so the loop continues with values from the previous iteration.

Check if `m_mountpoint` is empty before proceeding with statfs() and friends.
